cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.AI. 

The paper deals with content-based medical image retrieval using deep learning techniques, specifically deep convolutional neural networks (CNNs). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves information retrieval (IR) techniques, which makes cs.IR (Information Retrieval) another likely category. The use of multiple modalities in medical imaging suggests cs.MM (Multimedia) as another possible category. The use of deep learning techniques for classification and retrieval tasks suggests cs.LG (Machine Learning) as another possible category. Finally, the use of deep learning techniques for classification and retrieval tasks in the medical domain suggests cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as another possible category.
